Source: cl-portable-aserve
Section: web
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Kevin M. Rosenberg <kmr@debian.org>
Standards-Version: 3.5.7.0
Build-Depends-Indep: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)

Package: cl-aserve
Architecture: all
Depends: common-lisp-controller (>= 3.36), cl-acl-compat, cl-htmlgen
Description: Portable Aserve
 A portable version of AllegroServe which is a web application server
 for Common Lisp programs.

Package: cl-acl-compat
Architecture: all
Depends: common-lisp-controller (>= 3.36)
Recommends: cmucl-graystream
Description: Compatibility layer for Allegro Common Lisp
 A thin compatibility-layer that emulates Allegro Common Lisp. It is used
 to support a number of Allegro's open-source packages.

 This package requires cmucl-graystream to work with CMUCL. But, that
 package is not required to allow cl-acl-compat to be installed on
 platforms that do not support CMUCL.

Package: cl-htmlgen
Architecture: all
Depends: common-lisp-controller (>= 3.36)
Description: HTML generation library for Common Lisp programs
 A flexible library to generate HTML from Common Lisp programs.
